      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic constitutive model appropriate for metallic implant components loaded below yield; contact formulation captures screw-rod and rod-block interfaces without artificial stiffening.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V and 316L SS components modelled as isotropic linear elastic (E, nu from ASTM standards). Augmented Lagrange contact at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces with friction coefficient 0.2 (literature-derived). Model form is appropriate for quasi-static sub-yield loading regime. Plasticity model not required at this load level; confirmed by maximum von Mises stress below 0.85 yield strength in all constructs."
    },
    {
