      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the regulatory submission claims and to clinically meaningful failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force is the primary safety-critical QoI linked to implant fracture risk; force at 40 mm characterises post-yield behaviour relevant to revision surgery planning. All three QoIs are explicitly required by ASTM F1717 and referenced in the 510(k) submission claims. Relevance is fully established."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
