    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted given that ASTM F1717 prescribes a single offset distance and the regulatory context does not require multi-configuration testing. The primary validation result (vr-01) demonstrates agreement within pre-established acceptance bounds for all three QoIs. The supplementary validation result (vr-02) is noted to use a dynamically-loaded comparator inconsistent with the quasi-static COU; this comparator mismatch constitutes an undercutting defeater but does not affect the overall acceptance decision because the primary result (vr-01) is independently sufficient to support the credibility claim. Overall credibility is judged adequate for a Medium assurance level, Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence context.",
